[This outbreak of invasive group A streptococcal (iGAS) infection (32 cases with now 13 deaths, which had been previously 12 deaths, since February 2019) is reported to be occurring in Essex, a county in the southeast of England, northeast of London (https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Essex). Cases are occurring mainly in the Essex districts of Braintree (population 147 084 residents), with smaller numbers in Maldon (population 64 000 residents) and Chelmsford (population 176 200 residents) and a few cases are occurring in other Essex districts; see previous ProMED-mail post Streptococcus, group A, invasive - UK: (England) fatal, RFI
Archive Number: 20190628.6542184.

A map of England showing the location of Essex can be found at https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Essex and a map of Essex showing the location of these districts can be found at https://www.mapsofworld.com/england/counties/essex-map.html; according to this map, Braintree and Chelmsford appear to be located in mid Essex and Maldon in east Essex.

The above news report says that whole genome sequencing of the clinical isolates of GAS has identified an outbreak strain and has linked cases occurring in west Essex and mid Essex. - Mod.ML

